  "page": "Kayce",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #DEDEE2;\">Kayce</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\nWalled town and castle</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Location</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westerlands</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Government</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\">House Kenning</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Feudalism\" title=\"Feudalism\">feudal lord</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Ruler</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Terrence_Kenning\" title=\"Terrence Kenning\">Terrence Kenning</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Founded</th><td>\nby <a href=\"/index.php/Gundor_Goodbrother\" title=\"Gundor Goodbrother\">Gundor Goodbrother</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Age_of_Heroes\" title=\"Age of Heroes\">Age of Heroes</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Gundor_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gundor-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:402px;\">\n<div style=\"position: relative; border: 1px solid lightgray\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Westerlands.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"The westerlands and the location of Kayce\"><img alt=\"The westerlands and the location of Kayce\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7f/The_Westerlands.png/400px-The_Westerlands.png\" width=\"400\" height=\"444\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7f/The_Westerlands.png/600px-The_Westerlands.png 1.5x, /images/7/7f/The_Westerlands.png 2x\" /></a><div style=\"position: absolute; z-index: 2; top: 53.9%; left: 10.6%; height: 0; width: 0; margin: 0; padding: 0;\"><div style=\"position: relative; text-align: center; left: -8px; top: -8px; width: 15px; font-size: 15px;\"><img alt=\"The westerlands and the location of Kayce\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/15px-Red_pog.png\" title=\"Kayce\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/23px-Red_pog.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b4/Red_pog.png/30px-Red_pog.png 2x\" /></div><div style=\"font-size: 120%; line-height: 110%; z-index:90; position: relative; top: -1.5em; width: 6em; left: 0.5em; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"padding: 1px;\"></span></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumbcaption\">The <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> and the location of Kayce\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><table>\n\n<tbody><tr><td></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Kayce</b> is the seat of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\">House Kenning of Kayce</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasosappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The castle<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and walled<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> town<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> are located along the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Sea\" title=\"Sunset Sea\">Sunset Sea</a> on a peninsula south of <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a> and west of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Feastfires\" title=\"Feastfires\">Feastfires</a> is located nearby to the southwest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafwesteros.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Ancient_History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ancient History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#House_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">House Targaryen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Recent_History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent History</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to semi-canon sources, Kayce is a walled port town<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gundor_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gundor-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> with a castle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ancient_History\">Ancient History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Ancient History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>According to a semi-canon source, Kayce was founded by <a href=\"/index.php/Gundor_Goodbrother\" title=\"Gundor Goodbrother\">Gundor Goodbrother</a>, an <a href=\"/index.php/Ironman\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ironman\">ironman</a>, when <a href=\"/index.php/House_Casterly\" title=\"House Casterly\">House Casterly</a> held <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gundor_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gundor-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Kayce was held by ironborn during the era of the <a href=\"/index.php/Driftwood_king\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Driftwood king\">driftwood kings</a>. The town changed hands when <a href=\"/index.php/Herrock_the_Whoreson\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Herrock the Whoreson\">Herrock the Whoreson</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Harlaw\" title=\"House Kenning of Harlaw\">Kenning of Harlaw</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafkayce.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> used <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Herrock\" title=\"Horn of Herrock\">his horn</a> to signal the <a href=\"/index.php/Whores\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whores\">whores</a> of the town to open a postern gate, allowing Herrock's men to enter the town. The region was then ruled by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Kenning_of_Kayce\" title=\"House Kenning of Kayce\">House Kenning of Kayce</a> as part of the dominion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Rock\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Rock\">Kings of the Rock</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a>. Three ironborn kings failed in their attempts to reclaim the town, with Herrock killing two of them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Targaryen\">House Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1d/Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg/300px-Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"273\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1d/Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg/450px-Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1d/Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg/600px-Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kaycemerchant_by_gabriela_birchal-FFG.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A merchant from Kayce, by Gabriela Birchal © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> visited Kayce in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_55_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">55&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to a semi-canon source, <a href=\"/index.php/Dalton_Greyjoy\" title=\"Dalton Greyjoy\">Dalton Greyjoy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"Lord of the Iron Islands\">Lord of the Iron Islands</a>, nearly captured Kayce during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Gundor_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Gundor-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and the widow of the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_Kayce\" title=\"Knight of Kayce\">Knight of Kayce</a> was taken by the Red Kraken as a <a href=\"/index.php/Salt_wife\" title=\"Salt wife\">salt wife</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Lannister\" title=\"Johanna Lannister\">Johanna Lannister</a> was focused on defending Kayce instead of involving the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> further in <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>'s civil war.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaftermath_-_the_hour_of_the_wolf.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>At the time of the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency of Aegon III Targaryen</a>, Johanna led a host from <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a>, routing the ironborn beneath the town's walls, with Dalton's uncle slain in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_at_Kayce\" title=\"Battle at Kayce\">battle at Kayce</a>. Songs claim Johanna slew twelve ironmen in the fighting, although scholars believe she only carried a banner.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a> sailed to confront Dalton, ironborn longships gathered along the <a href=\"/index.php/Sunset_Sea\" title=\"Sunset Sea\">Sunset Sea</a>, including Kayce. Dalton was assassinated at <a href=\"/index.php/Faircastle\" title=\"Faircastle\">Faircastle</a> before Alyn arrived in the west, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_voyage_of_alyn_oakenfist.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_History\">Recent History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Merchants from Kayce sought loans from <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> after the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Lord of Casterly Rock\">Lord of Casterly Rock</a> began to extend and forgive debts.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Sansa_Stark\" title=\"Sansa Stark\">Sansa Stark</a> spots Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kennos_of_Kayce\" title=\"Kennos of Kayce\">Kennos of Kayce</a> training in the yard of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Kennos carries the <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_of_Herrock\" title=\"Horn of Herrock\">Horn of Herrock</a> as part of Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime Lannister</a>'s host in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Kayce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<d